    <item>
      system      : "Linux"
      description : "SLES-12-010690 - All SUSE operating system files and directories must have a valid owner."
      info        : "Unowned files and directories may be unintentionally inherited if a user is assigned the same User Identifier (UID) as the UID of the unowned files."
      solution    : "Either remove all files and directories from the SUSE operating system that do not have a valid user, or assign a valid user to all unowned files and directories on the system with the 'chown' command:

# sudo chown <user> <file>"
